      "content": "Serous fluid is a normal part of the healing process, but even with that in mind, you should still be vigilant. Warm soak and Neosporin are good for now, but if the area doesn't start to look better in a couple of days or if you notice increased redness, swelling, or a foul smell, it's time to seek medical attention. It's better to address these signs early to prevent complications. Trust me, it's not worth the risk. Keep an eye on it, and don't hesitate to call your doctor if things don't improve. Your health is the priority!",
